[{"id":"VH949191","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n\n<img alt=\"The figure presents two spheres, Sphere 1 and Sphere 2, that each have a charge of positive q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH949191.g01.png\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Isolated spheres 1 and 2 both carry positive charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q\"><math alttext=\"q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"italic\"><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, but sphere 2 has more mass than sphere 1. The objects are released from rest when they are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></math></span></span> apart and accelerate away from each other. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U\"><math alttext=\"U\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow></math></span></span> be the electric potential energy of the system of two spheres, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"K sub 1\"><math alttext=\"K sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>K</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"K sub 2\"><math alttext=\"K sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>K</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></math></span></span> be the kinetic energies of sphere 1 and sphere 2, respectively. Which of the following pairs of energy bar charts could represent the distribution of the energies in the system when the spheres are first released and the distribution of energies when the spheres are a large distance away from each other?</p>","rubricRef":"VH949191_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two energy bar charts with three categories each, as foll